00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:11.740
Next dish is another
favorite of mine.

00:13:11.740 --> 00:13:16.340
It's basically roasted
carrots with burrata.

00:13:16.340 --> 00:13:20.340
Roasting is sometimes quite
scary for people, right?

00:13:20.340 --> 00:13:23.152
Who likes roasting carrots
and veggies and-- oh,

00:13:23.152 --> 00:13:24.360
you're all pretty good, then.

00:13:24.360 --> 00:13:24.859
Nice.

00:13:24.859 --> 00:13:25.960
It was just me, then.

00:13:25.960 --> 00:13:26.490
Oh well.

00:13:30.220 --> 00:13:32.420
The reason why I think
people are very fearful

00:13:32.420 --> 00:13:36.000
of cooking veggies,
or not successful,

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:38.670
is that sometimes they
cut them too small.

00:13:38.670 --> 00:13:40.940
So by the end of it,
they're all shriveled up.

00:13:40.940 --> 00:13:44.009
And there's no
substance to them.

00:13:44.009 --> 00:13:45.550
And then other times
they roast them,

00:13:45.550 --> 00:13:46.770
and they don't have any color.

00:13:46.770 --> 00:13:47.870
Because they're too small.

00:13:47.870 --> 00:13:49.070
Because then they're
going to overcook.

00:13:49.070 --> 00:13:50.153
And they're going to burn.

00:13:50.153 --> 00:13:54.600
So keeping your vegetables
a little bit more chunky

00:13:54.600 --> 00:13:57.270
allows you to be able to
get some more sweetness

00:13:57.270 --> 00:14:01.650
and caramelization from
the carrot, or the veg,

00:14:01.650 --> 00:14:02.990
without overcooking.

00:14:02.990 --> 00:14:06.140
So I like to just them
very gently in a pan.

00:14:08.890 --> 00:14:11.430
Just layer them up like this.

00:14:11.430 --> 00:14:13.750
Top and tail so you
can fit a few more in.

00:14:16.390 --> 00:14:18.280
You can throw some on
the top and stir them

00:14:18.280 --> 00:14:21.730
around again, too, if you want.

00:14:21.730 --> 00:14:26.840
And then just let them go
on a medium to high heat,

00:14:26.840 --> 00:14:30.250
depending on what kind
of veggies they are.

00:14:30.250 --> 00:14:32.740
And then get a nice
little color on them.

