Really amazing.

00:22:56.550 --> 00:22:58.280
So yeah, this is it.

00:22:58.280 --> 00:23:02.440
Using broccoli stalks-- do
you guys eat broccoli stalks?

00:23:02.440 --> 00:23:07.610
Yeah, just using those up,
not throwing them away,

00:23:07.610 --> 00:23:10.670
just maybe peeling the
outer part of the broccoli,

00:23:10.670 --> 00:23:13.580
because sometimes
that's the toughest.

00:23:13.580 --> 00:23:15.900
So it's basically knowing
when to use something

00:23:15.900 --> 00:23:17.360
and when not to.

00:23:17.360 --> 00:23:19.135
If something's
tough, peel it back.

00:23:19.135 --> 00:23:21.510
Because if it's tough, then
you're not going to enjoy it.

00:23:21.510 --> 00:23:27.010
But if it's tender and sweet and
beautiful, feel free to use it.

00:23:27.010 --> 00:23:27.650
OK.

00:23:27.650 --> 00:23:32.220
So when these come out
of the oven, again,

00:23:32.220 --> 00:23:35.080
you've just concentrated
all that sweetness.

00:23:35.080 --> 00:23:37.240
You can see the theme.

00:23:37.240 --> 00:23:38.310
The carrots are nice.

00:23:38.310 --> 00:23:41.110
They should be a little bit
salty and a little bit sweet,

00:23:41.110 --> 00:23:43.740
a little bit herbaceous
from the earthy rosemary

00:23:43.740 --> 00:23:46.515
and a little bit of the
garlic from the roasted garlic

00:23:46.515 --> 00:23:48.300
that you put in.

00:23:48.300 --> 00:23:55.260
I really just tap each carrot
with just a touch of lemon.

00:23:55.260 --> 00:23:57.720
Because again, the sweetness
you've concentrated.

00:23:57.720 --> 00:23:59.800
You've got some nice color.

00:23:59.800 --> 00:24:02.660
You've got all that flavor
rocking and working.

00:24:07.950 --> 00:24:09.502
Really take your
time to do this.

00:24:09.502 --> 00:24:10.960
Because you don't
want to miss one.

00:24:10.960 --> 00:24:14.240
Because then somebody might
get the one that's not dressed.

00:24:14.240 --> 00:24:16.910
And then they're not having
the same experience as you.

00:24:16.910 --> 00:24:22.020
So being nice and balanced is
really important, and thinking

00:24:22.020 --> 00:24:24.320
about the other person, too.

00:24:24.320 --> 00:24:26.430
Again, just fresh olive oil.

00:24:26.430 --> 00:24:29.520
She's still on her phone.

00:24:29.520 --> 00:24:30.460
She's going to leave.

00:24:30.460 --> 00:24:32.043
She's going to be
like, what happened?

00:24:32.043 --> 00:24:33.360
[LAUGHS]

00:24:34.170 --> 00:24:37.200
So just give it a
little light toss

00:24:37.200 --> 00:24:39.750
in the remaining olive oil.

00:24:39.750 --> 00:24:40.710
And just arrange it.

00:24:40.710 --> 00:24:41.375
Look how cute.

00:24:41.375 --> 00:24:44.130
Do you see these
little crispy bits?

00:24:44.130 --> 00:24:46.520
It's no point
chopping those off.

00:24:46.520 --> 00:24:48.230
I don't like it when
you go to a place

00:24:48.230 --> 00:24:50.604
and it doesn't look like what
it's supposed to look like.

00:24:50.604 --> 00:24:52.940
I love keeping
things very organic.

00:24:52.940 --> 00:24:58.840
And if it's a carrot, make
it look like a carrot instead

00:24:58.840 --> 00:25:01.330
of making these little squares.

00:25:01.330 --> 00:25:04.690
I love rustic, but
delicious food.

00:25:04.690 --> 00:25:07.390
OK So I've got that down.

00:25:07.390 --> 00:25:09.880
And I've got some burrata
which is from Italy.

00:25:09.880 --> 00:25:12.130
It's basically a mozzarella.

00:25:12.130 --> 00:25:14.550
So they make a mozzarella sack.

00:25:14.550 --> 00:25:17.730
And they shove it full
of sometimes cream

00:25:17.730 --> 00:25:21.030
or creme fraiche and this thing
called stracciatella, which

00:25:21.030 --> 00:25:23.520
is just shreds of mozzarella.

00:25:23.520 --> 00:25:25.570
So basically, it's got
this nice little coat.

00:25:25.570 --> 00:25:27.710
You guys can see it here.

00:25:27.710 --> 00:25:30.590
Nice little skin of
mozzarella on the outside.

00:25:30.590 --> 00:25:34.770
And then this lovely, oozy,
gooey, cheesy goodness inside.

00:25:34.770 --> 00:25:38.190
So I get really excited
about that kind of stuff.

00:25:38.190 --> 00:25:40.370
It's what makes my day.

00:25:40.370 --> 00:25:42.740
You just pick this up.

00:25:42.740 --> 00:25:45.671
It doesn't matter
if some oozes out.

00:25:45.671 --> 00:25:50.490
Just arrange it nicely
on the plate like that.

00:25:50.490 --> 00:25:54.270
And you get this contrast
between this lovely white cream

00:25:54.270 --> 00:25:58.480
and then these beautiful
golden carrots.

00:25:58.480 --> 00:26:01.210
Let's take a look at
these, by the way.

00:26:01.210 --> 00:26:03.340
They're getting there.

00:26:03.340 --> 00:26:05.942
And you can speed
this process up.

00:26:05.942 --> 00:26:08.275
I'm a little scared of this
induction, just so you know.

