00:29:52.114 --> 00:29:53.572
AUDIENCE: When you
were growing up,

00:29:53.572 --> 00:29:56.710
did you always like vegetables?

00:29:56.710 --> 00:29:57.950
Sorry, two parts.

00:29:57.950 --> 00:30:00.530
And then also, what were
your biggest influences

00:30:00.530 --> 00:30:02.455
with vegetables growing up?

00:30:02.455 --> 00:30:03.330
APRIL BLOOMFIELD: OK.

00:30:03.330 --> 00:30:05.330
So yeah, I loved
veggies growing up.

00:30:05.330 --> 00:30:09.070
My Nan, actually, was the
best cook in the family.

00:30:09.070 --> 00:30:12.380
And we always used to go
round to have a big roast

00:30:12.380 --> 00:30:14.490
dinner, a big roast lunch.

00:30:14.490 --> 00:30:16.862
And she was amazing.

00:30:16.862 --> 00:30:18.320
She would get all
her mise en place

00:30:18.320 --> 00:30:20.300
in little pots on the stove.

00:30:20.300 --> 00:30:23.000
She'd have her peeled
potatoes covered in water.

00:30:23.000 --> 00:30:27.320
She'd have her parsnips in a
pan ready to go in the oven.

00:30:27.320 --> 00:30:29.630
And that was very inspiring.

00:30:29.630 --> 00:30:30.990
She was very organized.

00:30:30.990 --> 00:30:33.700
But yeah, I loved
roasted carrots.

00:30:33.700 --> 00:30:35.220
I loved carrots.

00:30:35.220 --> 00:30:36.260
I love potatoes.

00:30:36.260 --> 00:30:39.590
I think I must have some
Irish in me somewhere.

00:30:39.590 --> 00:30:41.870
I'm slightly obsessed
about potatoes.

00:30:41.870 --> 00:30:44.800
But peas, I love peas.

00:30:44.800 --> 00:30:46.240
Parsnips.

00:30:46.240 --> 00:30:50.680
Parsnips were a little bit more
difficult. But I did eat them,

00:30:50.680 --> 00:30:52.810
just because they were
a bit more floral.

00:30:52.810 --> 00:30:55.355
But I worked in a restaurant
called The River Cafe where

00:30:55.355 --> 00:30:58.370
I really got to
experience things

00:30:58.370 --> 00:31:01.880
like parsnips and celeriac or
fennel, that a lot of people

00:31:01.880 --> 00:31:02.687
don't like.

00:31:02.687 --> 00:31:04.520
Because I think they
struggle with that kind

00:31:04.520 --> 00:31:08.002
of floral, aromatic
flavor that they have.

00:31:08.002 --> 00:31:08.710
And I don't know.

00:31:08.710 --> 00:31:10.090
They really just opened my eyes.

00:31:10.090 --> 00:31:13.240
And I fell in love with
that type of vegetable

00:31:13.240 --> 00:31:14.640
at that restaurant.

00:31:14.640 --> 00:31:18.005
And so I think you can kind
of see that come through

00:31:18.005 --> 00:31:19.370
in the book.

00:31:19.370 --> 00:31:22.754
